IV. EMERGENCE: How 5 Makes 6

When two relationships co-activate a facet,
their tensor entries interfere constructively:

Emergent Facet fₑ = Σ(Rᵢⱼ * Rᵢₖ)

This produces a new facet not present in the base set.

That’s how:
	•	5 relationships create a 6th identity state
	•	2 incomplete ideas form a complete doctrine
	•	2/3 + 2/3 = emergent 6
	•	father + son + love = new mode of self
	•	operator + mission + time = warrior-architect
	•	Pantheon daemons cross-activate → new subsystem

Emergence is simply tensor multiplication within the relationship field.

